This paper describes a digital humanities system designed for text mining and analysis, which involves information retrieval (IR), natural language processing (NLP), and data storage and management. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). The paper also mentions the implementation of a database, which suggests the relevance of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
